#Approach:

Floor and Ceil in Sorted Array – Binary Search Approach

Floor ka matlab:
Array ka sabse bada element jo <= x ho.

Ceil ka matlab:
Array ka sabse chhota element jo >= x ho.

Dono ko binary search se efficiently nikal sakte hain.

Floor ke liye:
Binary search lagao.
Agar nums[mid] <= x:
    Ye possible floor ho sakta hai,
    isliye floor = nums[mid] store karo
    aur right side me search karo (low = mid + 1)
Else:
    Left side me jao (high = mid - 1)

Ceil ke liye:
Binary search lagao.
Agar nums[mid] >= x:
    Ye possible ceil ho sakta hai,
    isliye ceil = nums[mid] store karo
    aur left side me search karo (high = mid - 1)
Else:
    Right side me jao (low = mid + 1)

Agar floor ya ceil na mile to -1 return karo.

Time Complexity: O(log n)
Space Complexity: O(1)


#Code:

class Solution {
    public int[] getFloorAndCeil(int[] nums, int x) {
        int n = nums.length;
        int floor = -1;
        int ceil = -1;

        int low = 0, high = n - 1;

        // Find Floor
        while(low <= high){
            int mid = low + (high - low) / 2;
            if(nums[mid] <= x){
                floor = nums[mid];
                low = mid + 1;
            } else {
                high = mid - 1;
            }
        }

        // Reset for Ceil
        low = 0;
        high = n - 1;

        // Find Ceil
        while(low <= high){
            int mid = low + (high - low) / 2;
            if(nums[mid] >= x){
                ceil = nums[mid];
                high = mid - 1;
            } else {
                low = mid + 1;
            }
        }

        return new int[]{floor, ceil};
    }
}
